cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about document ranking using neural word embeddings. The most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper specifically addresses the problem of identifying relevant documents given a query. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of neural networks and machine learning techniques makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves data analysis and statistical modeling, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
